-- Egyptian Stocks: EFG-Hermes, Oriental Weavers, Sinai Cement
-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 2012-04-22T12:47:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-22/egyptian-stocks-efg-hermes-gb-auto-oriental-weavers.html
Egypt’s benchmark  EGX30 Index (EGX30)  rose
for a second day, gaining 2.6 percent to 4,829.12 at the 2:30
p.m. close in Cairo. That’s the biggest advance in more than two
months.  The following shares were active on the Egyptian Exchange.
Stock symbols follow company names.  EFG-Hermes Holding SAE (HRHO)   jumped 6 percent, the most
in almost two months, to 12.19 Egyptian pounds. The brokerage
unit of the largest publicly traded Arab investment bank was
accredited by the  Dubai Financial Market  for margin trading.  Oriental Weavers Co. (ORWE)   climbed 8.6 percent, the
most since July 2010, to 19.54 pounds. Shareholders of Egypt’s
biggest carpets producer approved a dividend distribution of 1.5
pounds a share.  Sinai Cement (SCEM)   rose 1.6 percent to 30.4 pounds, the
highest level in more than two weeks. The Cairo-based cement
producer will pay shareholders on record today a dividend of 3
pounds a share.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
